# AI ASSISTANT

The dashboard must include a built-in AI Assistant.

The AI is not responsible for programming the bot or editing source code directly. Instead, it serves as an intelligent helper that answers questions about the dashboard and guides administrators through every feature.

The AI should understand all dashboard settings and explain them clearly.

Examples:

"What does Claim Ticket do?"

"How can I create a new ticket panel?"

"Why can't users open tickets?"

"How do I change the support role?"

"Where do transcripts get saved?"

"What permissions are missing?"

"How do I create a purchase ticket?"

The AI should provide accurate explanations and step-by-step guidance.

It should also suggest better settings and identify common configuration mistakes.

